Ex. No.:02
PLANNING A REAL APPLICATIONS
Date : 31/07/2024
Aim:
To develop a React component that collects a user’s name through an input field and displays
it after submission, creating an interactive welcome screen.
Procedure:
1. Set Up the React Project:
• Create a new React project using Vite or create-react-app.
• Open the project folder and navigate to App.js.
2. Code Explanation:
• Import the useState hook from React to manage state.
• Create two state variables: name to hold the input value, and submittedName to store
the submitted name.
• Define handleInputChange to update name with each keystroke.
• Define handleSubmit to set submittedName with the current name value and then
clear the input field.
3. Build the UI:
• Create a centered div with a heading that welcomes users to SRMIST MCA.
• Add an input field with a placeholder to prompt the user to enter their name.
• Add a submit button to confirm the name input.
• Display the submitted name below the button once it is entered.
4. Run the Application:
• Save the changes.
• Start the development server using npm start.
• Open the application in the browser to test the input functionality.
4
Source code:
import { useState } from 'react';
function App() {
const [name, setName] = useState(''); // To store the name entered by the user
const [submittedName, setSubmittedName] = useState(''); // To store the submitted name
const handleInputChange = (event) => {
setName(event.target.value); // Update the name as the user types
};
const handleSubmit = () => {
setSubmittedName(name); // Save the name when the user clicks the button
setName(''); // Optionally clear the input after submission
};
return (
<div style={{ display: 'flex', flexDirection: 'column', justifyContent: 'center', alignItems: 'center',
height: '100vh' }}>
<h1>
WELCOME TO <span style={{ color: 'blue' }}>SRMIST</span> MCA
</h1>
<input
type="text"
placeholder="Enter your name"
value={name}
onChange={handleInputChange}
style={{ marginTop: '20px', padding: '10px', fontSize: '16px' }}
/>
<button onClick={handleSubmit} style={{ marginTop: '10px', padding: '10px 20px', fontSize:
'16px' }}>
Submit
</button>
5
{submittedName && (
<p style={{ marginTop: '20px', fontSize: '18px' }}>
Name Entered: <strong>{submittedName}</strong>
</p>
)}
</div>
);
}
export default App;
Output:
6
Result:
The application displays a welcome message with "SRMIST" in blue and an input field
prompting users to enter their name. When submitted, the entered name is displayed on the screen in a
message, confirming the submission. This provides a user-friendly, interactive welcome
page for SRMIST MCA.
